res from set #0 + period, group_id, valance_main, fusion_heat, evaporation_heat, heat_of_formation, etc. | Leave-no-information-behind approach for deep neural networks |\n| 2 | `2_phonon_PROVEN_best10.csv` | **Top-10 proven features** from high-impact phonon ML papers | 10 | atomic_weight, density, atomic_radius, covalent_radius_cordero, en_pauling, electron_affinity, ionization_energy, dipole_polarizability, thermal_conductivity, specific_heat, imat_cohesive_energy | Explicitly identified as strongest predictors in major studies |\n| 3 | `3_thermo_mechanical.csv` | **Pure thermo-mechanical properties** - Ideal for sound velocity and Debye temperature | 8 | density, atomic_weight, specific_heat, thermal_conductivity, melting_point, boiling_point, fusion_heat, evaporation_heat | Phonons are lattice vibrations governed by mass, density, and thermal properties |\n| 4 | `4_electronic_bonding.csv` | **Electronic and bonding descriptors** - Best for ionic/covalent materials | 6 | en_pauling, electron_affinity, ionization_energy, dipole_polarizability, heat_of_formation, imat_cohesive_energy | Electronegativity difference controls lattice stiffness and optical modes |\n| 5 | `5_geometry_radius_volume.csv` | **Pure geometric descriptors** - Critical when interatomic distance dominates | 6-7 | atomic_radius, atomic_radius_rahm, covalent_radius_cordero, vdw_radius, atomic_volume, lattice_constant | Phonon frequency ∝ √(k/m), where k depends on bond length |\n| 6 | `6_magpie_features_only.csv` | **Full Magpie feature set** - Gold standard in materials informatics | 50-60 | All columns starting with magp_ | Magpie features consistently outperform others in property prediction |\n| 7 | `7_imat_features.csv` | **iMat/Materials Project descriptors** - Computed from DFT | 10-15 | All columns starting with imat_ | High-quality ab-initio-derived features from Materials Project |\n| 8 | `8_ULTRA_compact_strong.csv` | **Ultra-compact but powerful** - Ideal for fast models and real-tim